    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>For Summer, Fast Food From the Sea</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Florence Fabricant</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Fabricant, Florence</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Fresh sardines are available in some Manhattan supermarkets and speciality stores; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Slather some fresh sardines (that have been gutted but not boned) with good olive oil, tuck some herbs in the cavities and set them on a hot grill. In minutes you will have a summer feast that, with some slices of ripe tomato and a wedge of lemon, may transport your imagination to St.-Tropez or a port in Morocco. Fresh sardines are now about $4 to $5 a pound (six to eight fish) in several fish markets, including Fairway, Agata &amp; Valentina Citarella and Balducci's.</p>
      </block>
